article.headline: Murray State 77, Jacksonville St. 61
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Trey Pearson scored 22 points to help lead Murray State to a 77-61 victory over Jacksonville State on Saturday night. Pearson shot 8-of-16, including five 3-pointers, as Murray State (8-6, 2-2 Ohio Valley Conference) kept the Gamecocks (4-12, 0-4) winless in the league. Shawn Witherspoon scored 14 points and grabbed a game-high 10 rebounds for the Racers, who dominated the boards 38-25. Charles Johnson added 13 points and Justin Orr had 11. Tim Lewis shot 6-of-7 from behind the arc to build his team-high 19 points for the Gamecocks, who dropped their 10th straight game. B.J. Spencer added 14. The Gamecocks held the lead for the first 9 minutes of the game, until Witherspoon scored on a 15-foot jumper to put Murray State ahead, 13-12. The Racers used an 18-4 surge to take a 44-30 halftime lead. Murray State shot 52.2 percent over the final 20 minutes, hitting 12-of-23.
